cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a generalization of first-order logic and discusses axiomatization and completeness results for several natural classes of such logics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the expressive power of the language in comparison with coalgebraic hybrid logics, which are often used in AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper discusses model-theoretic constructions and results, which are relevant to machine learning. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper discusses ultraproducts, which are a mathematical concept relevant to data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility as the paper discusses a sequent system and establishes a syntactic cut-elimination result, which are relevant to programming languages.
